<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-99] Surefire plugin fails if JUnit is not available</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-99</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Surefire Plugin fails with the following message, if JUnit is not available on the test classpath:&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;INFO&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; No Java test frameworks found&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means, that you have to include JUnit in the classpath, even for projects that do not have any unit-tests (e.g. ressource projects or your first Hello World project).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
